16
00:00:36.220 --> 00:00:37.820
Let's examine these
layers one at a time.

17
00:00:38.820 --> 00:00:40.595
Layer one is the
network access layer.

18
00:00:40.595 --> 00:00:43.010
The network access layer
deals with creation of

19
00:00:43.010 --> 00:00:45.680
data packets and their
transmission across a network.

20
00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:47.780
This includes hardware
devices connected to

21
00:00:47.780 --> 00:00:49.520
physical cables and switches

22
00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:51.790
that direct data
to its destination.

23
00:00:52.790 --> 00:00:54.210
Layer two is the internet layer.

24
00:00:54.210 --> 00:00:56.930
The internet layer is where
IP addresses are attached to

25
00:00:56.930 --> 00:00:58.160
data packets to indicate

26
00:00:58.160 --> 00:01:00.485
the location of the
sender and receiver.

27
00:01:00.485 --> 00:01:02.510
The internet layer also focuses

28
00:01:02.510 --> 00:01:04.705
on how networks
connect to each other.

29
00:01:04.705 --> 00:01:06.740
For example, data packets

30
00:01:06.740 --> 00:01:08.600
containing information
