37
00:01:23.270 --> 00:01:25.600
information about the
status of the connection.

38
00:01:25.600 --> 00:01:28.085
Activities of this layer
include error control,

39
00:01:28.085 --> 00:01:29.360
which ensures data is flowing

40
00:01:29.360 --> 00:01:31.265
smoothly across the network.

41
00:01:32.265 --> 00:01:33.890
Finally, at the
application layer,

42
00:01:33.890 --> 00:01:35.840
protocols determine
how the data packets

43
00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:38.345
will interact with
receiving devices.

44
00:01:38.345 --> 00:01:41.090
Functions that are organized
at application layer

45
00:01:41.090 --> 00:01:44.360
include file transfers
and email services.

